#: ../../docs/jobs/index.rst:3 321732e4cd9d46908451fb046a4a0f21

msgid "作业系统"
msgstr "jobs"

#: ../../docs/jobs/index.rst:5 bf81ced5ec834cee9f8dd2fb1389b540

msgid ""
"ChinaSRC-P通过Slurm调度系统进行资源和作业管理，提高运行效率，以此来完成程序的规范运行，最新文档参考 "
"[Slurm官网](https://slurm.schedmd.com/documentation.html)。"
msgstr ""
"CSRC-P runs jobs through the Slurm scheduling system to ensure the proper"
" execution of programs. For the latest documentation, please refer "
"to[Slurm official website](https://slurm.schedmd.com/documentation.html)"

#: ../../docs/jobs/index.rst:7 443ca2b5a83c4dad9a4af57e12842faf
msgid "所有需要运行的作业，无论是程序调试还是业务计算，都必须通过交互式并行srun、批量提交sbatch或分布式salloc命令提交，提交后可以使用相关命令查询作业状态。"
msgstr "All jobs that need to be run, whether it is program debugging or business calculation, must be submitted through the interactive parallel srun, batch submission sbatch or distributed salloc command. After submission, you can use the relevant command to query the job status."

#: ../../docs/jobs/index.rst:11 e49d118a43e6411d9a5dc022f3b6f5ee
msgid "本章节介绍了作业系统的基本使用方法，如果你是第一次接触作业系统，建议你先阅读 :ref:`slurm_intro` 章节。"
msgstr "This chapter introduces the basic usage of the job system. If you are new to the job system, it is recommended that you read the :ref:`slurm_intro` chapter first."

#: ../../docs/jobs/index.rst:13 72c04743e4984749ad0dddcdb983eb2d

msgid ""
"如果你顺利完成了上面的步骤，那么是否可以直接让服务器运行你的程序了呢？ "
"答案是不可以的，如果你在登录后直接运行程序，很抱歉，会被终止掉，这是因为登录节点是不允许运行程序的， 你需要使用作业调度系统 SLURM "
"来运行你的程序。 如果你留意登录之后显示的主机名，名为 workstation 的主机仅仅为用户提供了登录操作的平台， "
"但程序的运行需要交给它背后的计算节点们完成。那么如何告诉工作站来运行我们的程序？ "
"我们需要使用作业调度系统SLURM，它给我们提供了若干运行程序的方式， 在本章节里我们简要介绍最常用的方式：提交 SLURM "
"作业脚本的批处理方式。"
msgstr ""
"Writing SLURM Scripts  If you have successfully completed the previous "
"steps, can you directly run your program on the server? The answer is "
"no.Have you ever noticed the hostname displayed after logging in, named "
"'admin'? This host only provides users with login operations.However, the"
" execution of programs needs to be handed over to the computational nodes"
" behind it. So how do we instruct the workstation to run our program? We "
"need to use the job scheduling system, SLURM, which offers us several "
"ways to run programs. In this chapter, we will briefly introduce the most"
" commonly used method: submitting SLURM job scripts in batch mode."

#: ../../docs/jobs/index.rst:22 a53b99b522fc49548924c4279c16529e
msgid "请不要在登录节点上直接运行作业，以免影响其他用户的正常使用。"
msgstr "Please do not run jobs directly on the login node to avoid affecting the normal use of other users."

#~ msgid "首先需要编写一个 SLURM 脚本。"
#~ msgstr "First, you need to create an SLURM script."

#~ msgid "准备好 SLURM 脚本之后，使用"
#~ msgstr "After preparing the SLURM script, use the following steps"

#~ msgid "$ sbatch run.slurm"
#~ msgstr "$ sbatch run.slurm"

